-- Japan Ministry of Finance Website Hacked by Unknown Perpetrators
-- B y   T o r u   F u j i o k a
-- 2012-06-27T00:02:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/japan-ministry-of-finance-website-hacked-by-unknown-perpetrators.html
Japan’s Ministry of Finance said it
shut down part of its website yesterday after it was hacked.  The section that displays details of state-owned assets was
hacked, according to a Finance Ministry official who spoke on
condition of anonymity in accord with the ministry’s policy. The
official said an investigation is under way to discover who was
responsible for the intrusion. NHK and  Kyodo News  were among
local media reporting the incident earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Toru Fujioka in Tokyo at 
